## Project memory (mnemo)

This project uses **mnemo** for shared, searchable memory. The curated
markdown under `.claude/` is the single source of truth; the search
index is built and kept current automatically by hooks.

**Before non-trivial work**, search the memory for prior decisions,
architecture and known pitfalls — use the `mnemo` MCP tool
`memory_search` (scope to `project`, and to your agent when relevant).
Do not re-investigate what is already recorded.

**After significant work or a decision**, record it in the curated
memory so it is not lost:
- general project knowledge → `.claude/memory/` (keep `MEMORY.md` a thin
  index; put detail in topic files; append day notes under `logs/`);
- agent-specific knowledge → `.claude/agent-memory/<agent>/`.

Rules:
- Edit only the `.md` files. **Never** edit the index database — it is
  disposable and rebuilt from the `.md`.
- The `.md` in git is the source of truth; the index is derived.
- Reindex is automatic (SessionStart / on memory edit / SessionEnd). To
  refresh on demand, the `mnemo` tool `memory_reindex` is available.

